          <h2>Buying your first guitar</h2>
          <p class="text-justify">Many beginners buy the first guitar that they think looks cool without knowing much about how it plays, so they end up with a guitar which does not sound great and doesn't play as comfortably as other awesome axes.</p>
          <p class="text-justify">Learn what to look for when buying your first guitar so that you can make the most informed decision and spend money on a guitar you are really happy with which keeps you playing for years!</p>
          <p><a class="btn btn-primary" href="/guitars" role="button">Learn About Guitars &raquo;</a></p>
        </div>
        <div class="col-lg-4">
          <h2>Buying your first effects</h2>
          <p class="text-justify">Every guitarist gets a creative sense as they improve their guitar playing and want to mimic the sounds of their favorite guitarists/bands or create a sound of their own. This requires a good knowledge of different effects pedals and how they perform for different genres.</p>
          <p class="text-justify">Learn which effects pedals offer the most bang for buck and provide a great deal of versatility for getting famous sounds from songs and for crafting your own sound.</p>
          <p><a class="btn btn-primary" href="/pedals" role="button">Learn About Effects &raquo;</a></p>
       </div>
        <div class="col-lg-4">
          <h2>Buying your first amplifier</h2>
          <p class="text-justify">A good amplifier brings everything together. It can make your guitar and your effects sound a little better, and it can give you the sound you've always wanted; however, not all amplifiers are good.</p>
          <p class="text-justify">Learn about what makes a good amplifier and what type of amplifier would be best suited for the sound that you are looking to achieve.</p>
          <p><a class="btn btn-primary" href="/amps" role="button">Learn About Amps &raquo;</a></p>
